Title : Michelangelo Sosnowitz
Text : '''Michelangelo Sosnowitz''' (born August 21, 1973) is an American music composer. His works include ballet, musical theater, electronic and popular music, as well as commercial, television and film. His feature film scores include [[A Novel Romance]], winner Best Film at the NYC International Independent Film Festival,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nyfilmvideo.net/content/view/529/124/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-06-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714145348/http://nyfilmvideo.net/content/view/529/124/ |archivedate=2014-07-14 |df= }}</ref> the [[Dan Fogler]] directorial debut [[Hysterical Psycho]] <ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1381597/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast</ref> and the [[Deborah Kampmeier]] film Split.<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3315656/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast</ref> His original ballet 'Petrouchka' won Best Choreography at NYMF 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/144197-NYMF-Gala-to-Honor-the-Weisslers-2010-Awards-for-Excellence-Winners-Announced |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-07-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022032829/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/144197-NYMF-Gala-to-Honor-the-Weisslers-2010-Awards-for-Excellence-Winners-Announced |archivedate=2012-10-22 |df= }}</ref> He wrote the opening theme music to [[The History Channel]] show [[Battles BC]] <ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1274788/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast</ref> and original theme music for ENTV, ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' BlackTreeMedia and other [[Penske Media Corporation|PMC]] programming. He also wrote the score and theme music to the [[Colin Quinn]] [[Web series]] COP SHOW. Original Off-Broadway musicals include Crazy Head Space <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/off-broadway/article/CRAZY-HEAD-SPACE-Announces-Cast-And-Crew-Show-Runs-31245-20090304#.U13AgK1dU4k |title=CRAZY HEAD SPACE Announces Cast And Crew, Show Runs 3/12-4/5 |publisher=Broadwayworld.com |date= |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref> and Love in the MIddle Ages.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/off-off-broadway/article/Dave-Konig-Mimi-Bessette-Yassmin-Alers-More-to-Star-in-LOVE-IN-THE-MIDDLE-AGES-at-Stage-72-20130926#.U13Au61dU4k |title=Dave Konig, Mimi Bessette, Yassmin Alers & More to Star in LOVE IN THE MIDDLE AGES at Stage 72 |publisher=Broadwayworld.com |date= |accessdate=2014-05-17}}</ref>

==Career==
Michelangelo began playing the piano at the age of five. His first published music happened in High School for a PBS Documentary called Oysters in the Long Island Sound in 1992. Also in 1992 Michelangelo won the Connecticut Songwriting Competition in its first year of inception. In 1993 and 1994 Michelangelo went to the [[Berkshire Theatre Festival]] and wrote songs and score for the Children's Theater. Michelangelo attended [[New York University]] studying at the [[Tisch School of the Arts]] and began composing music for student films, winning Best Score at the [[First Run Film Festival]] in 1996 for the film Soldier Boy and 1997 for the film Spirit.<ref>http://www.firstrunfestival.com/media/catalogs/1997catalogue.pdf</ref> As a composer Michelangelo wrote music for pop/rock bands featured on [[Satellite radio]] and [[Internet radio]] as well as numerous television commercials ranging from [[Animal Planet]], [[Acuvue]], [[Mercedes Benz]], [[Tervis Tumbler]], [[Garnier Fructis]] and [[Street King (drink)]]. Michelangelo also wrote extensive music for [[CONCACAF]] including their Champion's League theme and Gold Cup theme as well as stingers and promos.

==Original Theater/Musicals==
*"Crazy Head Space" (created and co-composed by Elisabeth Davis, lyrics by Elisabeth Davis; directed by Errickson Wilcox and Gabriel Barre)
*"Love in the Middle Ages" (book and lyrics by Eric Kornfeld; directed by Lisa Shriver)
*"Peking Roulette" (written by Ben Thompson; winner- best score Midtown International Theater Festival <ref>http://www.midtownfestival.org/bestofthefest2010.htm</ref>)

